{"name": "just-config", "metadata": {"name": "just-config", "version": "20.3", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "http://packages.python.org/just_config", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Minimalistic library to handle configuration for the application", "upload_time": 1732901845}, "documentation": ["# just_config\nMinimalistic library to handle configuration for the application.\n\nAs for now, it will look for the configuration value in the following order:\n  1.  In system environment variables.\n  2.  In `default.ini` file in the current working directory\n  3.  In `default.ini` file in application-specific folder under user home directory\n  \n## Usage:\n```python\n>>> from just_config.configuration import Configuration\n>>> cfg = Configuration()\n>>> cfg['test']\n'value'\n>>> # If I store my configuration in ~/.app/default.ini\n>>> cfg = Configuration('app')\n>>> cfg['test']\n'value'\n```\n\n## Example configuration file:\n```ini\n[DEFAULT]\ntest=value\n```\n\n![](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/just-config.svg)"], "modules": [{"name": "just_config", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "just_config.version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "just_config.version.VERSION", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "just_config.configuration", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "just_config.configuration._build_cfg_parser", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "just_config.configuration.Configuration", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "just_config.configuration.Configuration.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "app_n